              Using prediction error negativity features, we classified VR
              glitches with 77\% accuracy. We localized the EEG sources driving
              the classification and found midline cingulate EEG sources and a
              distributed network of parieto-occipital EEG sources to enable
              the classification success.Significance. Prediction error
              signatures from these sources reflect violations of user's
              predictions during interaction with AR/VR, promising a robust and
              targeted marker for adaptive user interfaces.",
